    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Once crispy, remove <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon</strong> and set it aside until later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for an initial 7-9 min</p><p>Slice your <strong>sugar snap peas</strong> into thirds</p><p>Once the pasta has been cooking for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat), add th<strong>e sliced sugar snap</strong>s and cook for 2-3 min further or until the pasta is cooked with a slight bite and the peas are tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and reserve a cup of<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced spring onion</strong> to the bacon pan and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to thicken</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> creamy sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>mint leaves</strong> finely, discard the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>cooked pasta</strong>, <strong>sugar snaps</strong>,<strong> reserved crispy bacon </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) through the creamy sauce and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy bacon & sugar snap pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: If the sauce is looking a little dry add a splash of the starchy pasta water</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-sugar-snap-and-mint-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon & sugar snap pasta </strong>in a bowl</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
